From: pawel@cs.UAlberta.CA (Pawel Gburzynski)
Subject: Re: login: shadow and lastlog won't work together??
Date: 29 Oct 93 19:21:26 GMT

jaggy@purplet.demon.co.uk (Mike Jagdis) writes:

>Use the shadow suite. Recompile finger paying particular attention to where 
>it looks for lastlog and what format it expects to see in there. Works for 
>me. Dunno what SLS's problem is.

Specifically do the following things:

1. Get the finger source from sunsite.unc.edu
   (/pub/Linux/system/Network/finger/finger.tar.Z)

2. Determine the size of an entry in your lastlog, e.g., by performing
   'od' and locating tty names.

3. Modify lastlog.h in finger's directory accordingly and move this file
   to /usr/include

4. Make and install the new finger.

I will bet that your entries are 12 bytes long and that
your favorite contents of lastlog.h are as follows:

#ifndef _lastlog_h
#define _lastlog_h

struct lastlog {
        long    ll_time;
        char    ll_line[7];
        char    ll_host[1];

/*  This was the default:
        char    ll_line[12];
        char    ll_host[16];    */      /* same as in utmp */
};

#endif /*!_lastlog_h*/

Regards,


