From: fyl@ssc.com (Phil Hughes)
Subject: What will "regular UNIX" users think of Linux
Date: Sat, 30 Oct 1993 00:54:30 GMT

Just thought of this and figured it might be of interest.

SSC's new catalog just came back from the printer today and it has
one page in it on Linux. Half the page is about SSC selling the Yggdrasil
distribution but the other half is about Linux, the Linux newsgroups and
ftp sites where people can get the code.

The first 15,000 of those catalogs will be mailed next week.  As SSC
hasn't been in the Linux business but most of our customers (probably 90%)
are UNIX users it should be interesting to see how many of these people
show up in these newsgroups or mention Linux when when order products
from SSC.  (We ask what UNIX version you run on the order form but, as far
as I know, there has never been a 'Linux' put in that blank.)
